                        <path class="slide__overlay-path" d="M0,0 150,0 500,405 0,405" />
                    </svg>
                        <div class="slide__text">
                            <h2 class="slide__text-heading">Dawki River</h2>
                            <p class="slide__text-desc">Dawki-Tamabil is one of the few road border crossings between India and Bangladesh. It is used mainly for coal transportation to Bangladesh. Some 500 trucks cross the border every day in peak season.
                            Some shared transport is available from Barabazar in Shillong to the border post at Dawki every morning. Buses are also available for the 70 kilometres (43 mi) journey from Shillong. On the other side inside Bangladesh the Tamabil bus station, 1.5 kilometres (0.93 mi) away, has regular bus service to Sylhet 55 kilometres (34 mi) away.</p>
        
