				<div class="col-lg-6 text-justify">
				<h1 class="shead-style text-center">MEGHALAYA</h1>
				<p>Known by nicknames such as Scotland of the east and the abode of clouds, Meghalaya is one of the seven northeastern states of India. One of the greenest places in India It receives one of the highest amounts of rainfall throughout the year. The climate is tropical in nature due to its position and geography. The landscape of Meghalaya is absolutely mesmerizing. Mostly consisting of hills and forests the state enjoys a cool and comfortable environment.</p><p>
        A hub for adventure activities many visitors visit Meghalaya from all corners of the world. Living root bridges are an important part of the major tourist attractions and many of these can be seen nearby Cherapunji. Also famous for their sacred groves the state has many such sacred groves throughout. These areas protected by the local people as a part of their folk culture. A visit throughout the rural areas gives a glimpse of the northeastern mountain life. Such villages attract many travelers due to its adventure activities.
        </p>
